text: Methicillin-resistant Staphylococcus aureus refers to a group of Gram-positive bacteria that are genetically distinct from other strains of Staphylococcus aureus. MRSA is responsible for several difficult-to-treat infections in humans.
The incubation period for MRSA often ranges from one to 10 days if it enters broken skin or damaged mucous membranes.
